      "review_summary": "The PR changes `resolveRunFailoverDecision` so harness-owned prompt timeouts return `fallback_model` when configured fallbacks exist instead of immediately surfacing the timeout error.\n\nPR surface: Source +9. Total +9 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level for the helper: current main exits before model fallback for harness-owned prompt timeouts, and the existing test matrix pins that behavior. The PR still lacks a live Ollama run proving the reported provider path should use this shared harness-owned branch.",
      "review_followup": "- [P2] Needs human review because the right fix depends on the maintainer-approved harness timeout boundary and a live/config-backed Ollama reproduction, not just a mechanical code change.",
